trainers.name: Sailor Roderic
trainers.dialogue: Ahoy there, landlubber! I once sailed through a storm so fierce even a Gyarados turned tail! You ever seen waves like that?

trainers.name: Fisher Jonas
trainers.dialogue: I caught a Feebas on the harbour!

trainers.name: Tobias
trainers.dialogue: Fresh imports! Pokéballs, exotic stones, and more!

trainers.name: Sailor Brendan
trainers.dialogue: We sailors love battles!

trainers.name: Jason
trainers.dialogue: I'm on the clock, no time for a battle!

trainers.name: Darius
trainers.dialogue: Careful near the warehouses at night. Some say there’s a gang running underground Pokémon battles, but me? I just move the boxes.

trainers.name: Sailor Briggs
trainers.dialogue: I've sailed to the faraway island of Crandor!

trainers.name: Fisher Hal
trainers.dialogue: The damn fish aren't biting today!

trainers.name: Mira
trainers.dialogue: The sea breeze here is the best in the whole region. I don’t think I could ever live inland.

trainers.name: Ken
trainers.dialogue: I came here to see the famous lighthouse…

trainers.name: Tuber Tyler
trainers.dialogue: When I grow up, I’m gonna be a Gym Leader! My team’s gonna be ALL Water-types!

trainers.name: Fisher Wyatt
trainers.dialogue: This is my private spot! Go away!

trainers.name: Zara
trainers.dialogue: You’d be amazed at what washes up here! Once, I even found a Heart Scale buried in the sand

trainers.name: Flint
trainers.dialogue: Move along kid!

trainers.name: Mandy
trainers.dialogue: Fresh-caught seafood makes the best dishes! Though, uh… don’t tell the Water-type trainers I said that.

trainers.name: Gwen
trainers.dialogue: I’ve lived here for over fifty years. The sea has changed, the people have changed… but the waves always return.

trainers.name: Reina
trainers.dialogue: We’ve been trading with far-off regions for decades.

trainers.name: Gale
trainers.dialogue: This port has been running since the days of the old Inisherin Fleet. Without us, half the region’s trade would dry up!

trainers.name: Eric
trainers.dialogue: Most people don’t know this, but some of these warehouses? They used to be part of the old defense network, back when pirates were a real threat.

trainers.name: Mikkel
trainers.dialogue: I hear stories every day. Some true, some not. But one keeps coming back—the tale of a ship that docks only on misty nights, with no crew aboard…

trainers.name: Clyde
trainers.dialogue: This sea’s full of secrets. I’ve seen shadows bigger than Wailord moving under my boat.

trainers.name: Becca
trainers.dialogue: Did you know some vacation homes here were built over an ancient ruin? Makes you wonder what’s still down there…

trainers.name: Officer Jack
trainers.dialogue: Stay away from the lighthouse, kid.

trainers.name: Liam
trainers.dialogue: Trainers passing through always talk about the deep-sea ruins nearby.

trainers.name: Lily
trainers.dialogue: Inisherin is the wealthiest town in the mainland because of our trade.

trainers.name: Geoff
trainers.dialogue: Hey kid, wanna buy some apples?

trainers.name: Ace Trainer Clyde
trainers.dialogue: I'm not in the mood for a battle right now.

trainers.name: Jax
trainers.dialogue: The market always has the freshest produce!

trainers.name: Greg
trainers.dialogue: Can you distract the fat guy while I steal an apple?

trainers.name: Tony
trainers.dialogue: My produce has been going missing...

trainers.name: Fergus
trainers.dialogue: When I was a young sailor, I saw a Pokémon with glowing eyes rise from the depths.
